  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does Cigna Global cover pre-existing conditions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cigna Global uses moratorium underwriting for individual plans. Pre-existing conditions aren't covered initially, but may become covered after 2 years without treatment for that condition. This differs from BUPA, which offers potential day-one coverage through full medical underwriting.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How long is the maternity waiting period?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cigna Global requires a 10-month waiting period for maternity coverage. You need to add the maternity benefit before conception to ensure delivery is covered. If you're already pregnant, maternity coverage cannot be added.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Cigna Global in the United States?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, but you need to add US coverage to your plan, which increases premiums by 40–60%. Without US coverage, you're only covered for emergencies in the US. With US coverage, you have full access to Cigna's domestic US network for routine and planned care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the difference between Silver, Gold, and Platinum?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Silver covers inpatient/hospital only. Gold adds full outpatient coverage (doctor visits, prescriptions, labs). Platinum adds enhanced benefits including better wellness coverage and higher limits on certain services. Most expats choose Gold as the best balance of coverage and cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Cigna's direct billing work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        At network hospitals and clinics, Cigna pays the provider directly. You show your Cigna ID card, pay any deductible or copay, and Cigna handles the rest. For planned procedures, call Cigna for pre-authorization—they'll confirm coverage and set up direct billing. At non-network providers, you pay upfront and submit for reimbursement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Cigna Global worth the cost?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cigna Global offers solid, comprehensive coverage backed by a Fortune 15 company. It's worth the cost if you value large provider networks, direct billing, strong customer service, and corporate-grade stability. It's not worth it if you're primarily budget-focused—competitors like IMG Global offer similar coverage at 30–40% less.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is a solid, reliable choice for international health insurance—particularly for corporate assignees, expat families, and those who value established infrastructure over lowest-possible pricing.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Bottom Line</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
      Cigna Global delivers what you'd expect from a major international insurer: comprehensive coverage, large provider networks, unlimited annual maximum, and responsive customer service. Their Fortune 15 backing means financial stability is never a concern.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-0">
      However, they're not the cheapest option, and their moratorium approach to pre-existing conditions is less flexible than competitors like BUPA. If budget is your primary constraint or you have conditions that need day-one coverage, explore alternatives. If you want a trusted name with proven infrastructure, Cigna Global is a safe choice.
    </p>
  </div>

